(1, 'Welcome to the RTA!', 'The Road To Angelo (RTA) Blog is a new blog that I am starting for my journey towards Angelo State University! I decided to start this blog to help me meet people, learn new things, help people with what I do know, and just to be used for something that I can use for accountability for my own selfish desires (yes I do have them...:P)[!--more--]\r\n<h2>My history with blogging</h2>\r\nI use to run a successful blog called The Creation Buzz (TCB) that was a blog for pretty much anything. I had about 100 subscribers to my RSS feed, more than an average of 200 hits a day, and I had content flowing in and out of that blog like it was nobody''s business. It was sure fun and a lot of hard work. I started to run into some complicated (too complicated to tell here) issues after about a year. I was somewhat forced to shut it down (sadly) due to too many spammed comments and other stuff I am not in the mood to talk about right now.\r\n\r\nBlogging has always been a passion of mine. I use to think that I was a Blogger for Passion Not Profit kind of person. Many good things came from blogging. I got to express my ideas. My goals. My thoughts. Cool things. Now I just hope that this blog goes as smooth as my last one. It should, after-all, I am using it to go to college with.\r\n<h2>What I plan to do</h2>\r\nI plan to use this blog to write at least one interesting topic a day that is going on in my life or on the road to angelo. I would like to share what I know in Linux since I am quite the linux junkie. Afterall, I am writing this blog entry from my newly installed Fedora 16 Linux Book. What? You don''t know what a Linux Book is? Well, I''ll tells ya! A Linux Book is a Net Book with Linux installed on it. Yeah. That is pretty straight forward. Anyways, I plan to have a dedicated page to Linux on this here blog. Maybe throw some cool content into it. You know: something I find on StumbledUpon, Twitter, Facebook, etc. Who knows what I will do with this blog.\r\n<h2>What do I think of the Internet?</h2>\r\nI think the Internet, or the Interwebs as I like to call it, is a place where one person could change his or her whole life with just one thing they say or do. I think that the Internet is a place to be someone. I think the Internet is place for businesses to reach thousands (or millions) of people for pennies. I think that the Internet is a place where you can hangout, meet new people, start something, learn new ideas, or just be yourself. Back in the mid 90s, I''m not saying I am old, people use to think "do I need to have a website?". Now a days, you wouldn''t think twice about owning and running a website, even a free wordpress or blogger blog. No I did not just steal that tidbit from <a title="The Amazing World of John Raasch!" href="http://www.Jonraasch.com" target="_blank">Jon Raasch</a>. By the way guys, check out this guys website! He is a freakin genius at web art thingy stuff! Just a shoutout to him. Anywho, I think the web is a place to be creative with your ideas and share them with the world.\r\n<h2>Anyways...</h2>\r\nNow it is time to wish all of you well, wish me well, and just go enjoy life. I will post and update all of you on the progress of my Road to Angelo! Keep comin back here!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'Angelo State University,ASU,Interwebs,John Raasch,my day,The Start,', '2012-03-23 14:22:41', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '03', '23', '14', '22', '41', 'yes', 'Published', 'yes', 'featured.jpg'),
(2, 'Semester Planning', 'Ah the joys of planning out what you need to take in order to move on with your life. Today I spent most of the day planning my year-long schedule at my current community college so that I can transfer out to Angelo State University.\r\n\r\nI began by finding out what I have taken, what I need to take, and what I could take at my current college. A lot of thinking. I finally narrowed it down to 8 more courses I can/need to take at this current college before going to ASU. I plan on taking 2 courses in the summer I 2012 and 2 courses in summer II 2012 (yeah I know...a lot to worry about plus part time work) then I will go about a full 4 course semester for the Fall of 2012 (yeah...I will do my best).[!--more--]\r\n\r\nThe thing about planning like this: is that you cannot simply just plan on paper, you need to do as well. How do you think I am going to do this? I will plan to study hard, work smart, and have fun (I guess). Well maybe not the have fun part because I can have fun later when I am at Angelo.\r\n\r\nThe rest of my day is going to consist of getting ready for work at 6:00p, I will leave by 5:30p, get there at 5:45p, work smart til 12a, then leave work and come home to relax while watching anime or playing some video game. Oh, you probably didn''t know I watched anime didn''t you? Well, there are a lot of things you need to know about me. You will find out over the course of a year.\r\n\r\nNow I am signing off to go enjoy myself before I go into work. Have fun, be safe, and watch out for baby chipmunks!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'chipmunks,my day,planning,semester planning,work,', '2012-03-24 18:16:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '03', '24', '18', '16', '44', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(3, 'Moving from one door to another', 'An the never ending process of going after something that you dream of. I am talking about going after a career that you want to have someday or job that you want to have just for a bit of spending money. I spent my day today waking up at about around 12p (yea I know...I''m a bit of a lazy bum. But you would be too if you stayed up til 3 am watching Oh My Goddess! and Blood+ episodes on Netflix), after getting up I went through my normal routine, and then did some College Algebra (that of which is not going to transfer to ASU...bummer), then worked on an online application for Gold\\''s Gym (I am wanting to drop out of the rat race of call center work and get into a better routine for a young college student who has no bills and no (needed) expenses), and then started writing this here blog entry for all of you (which is less that .00001%).[!--more--]\r\n<h2>What else do I have for you?</h2>\r\nYou want more from me? Hmm...well I did try to redo my iPad 2 by restoring it only to find out that when I try to sign in to Apple iTunes it keeps coming back with some weird user names and not letting me sign in. Weird. I will try it later.\r\n\r\nI also would like to play a bit of Maplestory for my own sick twisted mind. I also need to work on the overall appearance of this blog. That is pretty much it.\r\n<h2>The thing about moving to another door</h2>\r\nThere is something strange when moving from one position at a company to another less paid but better working condition position. It is a transition to a new thing. We all love new things. When it comes down to leaving this one $11 an hour job to going with schooling and maybe even a little $9 an hour part time job, I would miss the pay but seeing as though it is not needed in my life at this point I won''t miss it too much.\r\n\r\nWhen moving from one job to another you have to wonder about the people you use to work with, how are they going to do without you, did you leave such an impact on them that they will miss you?, how can you keep in touch with them?, and other questions like those stated above.\r\n\r\nI do like the position I am at but I honestly could do without work and focus on school at this point. School is more important and if I needed to work and make some money I could always go look for some part time work place thing.\r\n\r\nSo as of this blog I am saying that I will be leaving in about 9 weeks. Not to mention I have Tier 2 Training starting April 1st which means that I will have at least some Tier 2 experience that I can put on my resume for future prospect.\r\n\r\nNow I am going to go do some financial stuffs, play some maple, get ready for work, and hope for a good night! Stay beautiful everyone (all .00001% of you) and don''t do anything I wouldn''t do; but if you do then don''t name it after me. :)\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'another door,career path,education importance,golds gym,moving on,school,tier 2,', '2012-03-25 04:29:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '03', '25', '04', '29', '22', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(4, 'Livin from Paycheck to Paycheck', '<blockquote>I spent my life lookin'' for a discount. Now I thank God for the handout</blockquote>[!--more--]\r\n\r\nI was listenin'' to the song by Family Force 5 (Paycheck) and just thinking that I am blessed where I am right now. I have an almost $11 an hour job, going to school, about to go off to a nice university, and I don''t have to live from paycheck to paycheck.\r\n\r\nI bet a lot of people would like to be in my shoes which leads me to think that He has blessed me so that I can be a blessing to others. I try my best to help people out when they need it. All I can say is that I thank Him for blessing me with so much. Just thought I would post this.\r\n\r\nNathan\r\n<pre><span style="font-size: 1.5em;">Family Force 5 - Paycheck lyrics</span>\r\n\r\nI''m broke, broke as a joke\r\nThinking ''bout moving back in with my folks\r\nWalked away from my house note\r\nWatched my bank account go up in smoke\r\n\r\nIn a mess with the IRS,\r\nStill watching my movies on the VHS\r\nGod bless America\r\nI''m a gangsta thanks to ya\r\n\r\nI shoulda been a baller, shot-caller\r\nBut I''m just blue collar\r\nI got my job in Georgia\r\nTryin'' to get a piece of that peach cobbler\r\n\r\nChasing down that paper\r\nNeed a money-maker\r\n\r\nI spent my life lookin'' for a discount\r\nNow I thank God for the handout\r\n\r\nI can''t afford to live this way\r\nI barely live off what I make\r\nRunning round for money\r\nBegging on my knees\r\nLiving paycheck to paycheck to paycheck to paycheck\r\n\r\n3 sweaters, a coat, can''t keep my heat on\r\nI got nothing eat on\r\nNever heard of vacation\r\nI think they give those away on the radio station\r\n\r\nWork my fingers to the bone\r\nNo days off and I ain''t comin home\r\nI got a piece a paper in the mail today\r\nSaid I still got a balance that I got to pay\r\n\r\nI shoulda been a baller, shot-caller\r\nBut I''m just blue collar\r\nI got my job in Georgia\r\nTryin'' to get a piece of that peach