(5, 'How to install Google Chrome on Fedora 16 in 5 Easy Steps', 'We all love Google Chrome so much that we want it on every single operating system that we have. With the new Fedora 16 just being released, it (being Google Chrome) is now available to be used as a web browser. I know that this is blowing up all over the place but I would just like to point out some tricks that helped me to install Google Chrome on my Fedora 16 LinuxBook.[!--more--]\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>To learn how to do this correctly, follow the step by step instructions below.</strong>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<em>* = you will need to be root (or type in the root password) to use</em>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 1:</strong> First you start out by opening up the Terminal on your Fedora 16 (assuming that you have already fired up Fedora 16)\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 2:</strong> Next enter the follow into the Terminal window:\r\n<br />\r\n<code>wget https://dl-ssl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nThe above will use:\r\n<br />\r\n<code>wget</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nto install Google''s Signing Key for use in installing and running Google Chrome. I''m not quite sure what it does but I do believe to my knowledge it allows Chrome to run on Fedora.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>*Important:</strong>\r\n<br />\r\nIf you get:\r\n<br />\r\n<code>bash: wget: command not found</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nwhen you try to run the above line, run this in the Terminal to download wget\r\n<br />\r\n<code>sudo yum install wget</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nThis will install:\r\n<br />\r\n<code>wget</code>\r\n<br />\r\nso that you can then run the command from step 2.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>*Step 3:</strong> Next run this line in the Terminal:\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<code>sudo rpm --import linux_signing_key.pub</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nThis will install the signing key to your Fedora 16 installation\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>*Step 4:</strong> Now we need to add the repository. Type this into the Terminal:\r\n<br />\r\nAdd the following (in Step C) to:\r\n<br />\r\n<code><em>/etc/yum.repos.d/google.repo</em></code> file.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nNote: if you cannot find the <em>/etc/yum.repos.d/google.repo</em> file then first you need to create it.\r\n<h2>Here is how</h2>\r\n<strong>Step A:</strong> Open up a Terminal, then run this command\r\n<br />\r\n<code>sudo -i</code>\r\n<br />\r\nThis makes you the root.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step B:</strong> Type this into the Terminal:\r\n<br />\r\n<code>chmod 777 /etc/yum.repos.d/</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nWhat this does is it changes the permissions for the folder that we need to create the <em>google.repo</em> file to writable so that we can actually create the file.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nYou can then type:\r\n<br />\r\n<code>exit</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nin the terminal window to exit root. Note: you should never be root unless you know what you are doing.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step C:</strong> Next go into your <em>/etc/yum.repos.d/</em> directory and create a new file called <em>google.repo.</em>\r\n\r\nOnce you do that paste the information below, according to your Architecture, into the <em>google.repo</em> file and save it.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>For 32-bit</strong>\r\n<br />\r\n[google-chrome]\r\n<br />\r\nname=google-chrome - 32-bit\r\n<br />\r\nbaseurl=http://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/rpm/stable/i386\r\n<br />\r\nenabled=1\r\n<br />\r\ngpgcheck=1\r\n<br />\r\ngpgkey=https://dl-ssl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>For 64-bit</strong>\r\n<br />\r\n[google-chrome]\r\n<br />\r\nname=google-chrome - 64-bit\r\n<br />\r\nbaseurl=http://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/rpm/stable/x86_64\r\n<br />\r\nenabled=1\r\n<br />\r\ngpgcheck=1\r\n<br />\r\ngpgkey=https://dl-ssl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>*Step 5:</strong> Now we need to install the actual browser so type this into the Terminal:\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>To install the Stable version</strong>\r\n<br />\r\n<code>sudo yum install google-chrome-stable</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>To install the Beta version</strong>\r\n<br />\r\n<code>sudo yum install google-chrome-beta</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nYou can also install the unstable version if you would like to, personally I would not but if you want to test and debug it then be my guest.\r\n<br />\r\n<code>sudo yum install google-chrome-unstable</code>\r\n<br /><br />\r\nAnd there you have it! You have now installed Google Chrome on Fedora 16! Let me know if you need any help, I will be glad to help you.\r\n\r\nI hope you enjoyed my take on how to install Google Chrome for Fedora 16 and enjoy!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 3, 'Fedora,Fedora 16,Google Chrome,how to,install Google Chrome on Fedora 16,Linux,linux tutorials,', '2012-03-27 21:25:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '03', '27', '21', '25', '35', 'yes', 'Published', 'yes', 'featured.jpg'),
(6, 'The day of decisions, work, and installing stuff', 'Today started out like any normal Monday, getting up at about around 11:00 am, doing my normal routine, then going off to class (College Algebra) at 12:00 pm. After that class, I went to the Library (gasp...you go to the library?) to study some College Algebra (to which I got my homework due today done! A material), next up I went to go chill and unwind at the gym. Today''s workout was Back, Biceps, and Legs (ugh...) but it felt good.[!--more--]\r\n\r\nAfter the nice time at the gym I came home to write an article called <a title="How to install Google Chrome on Fedora 16 in 5 Easy Steps" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/how-to-install-google-chrome-on-fedora-16-in-5-easy-steps/">How to install Google Chrome on Fedora 16 in 5 Easy Steps</a>. I wanted to make my own version of it and I just learned how to do it so it seemed like a good idea. Now I am writing this article, trying to install OpenOffice on my Fedora 16 LinuxBook (harder than what it seems), and about to get ready for work at 6:00 pm. Oh? Work last night? It went well. Got a few good calls in, became hooked with trying to learn how to solve the Rubik''s Cude (2x2x2), learning Cube Notation, and getting better at what I do.\r\n\r\nI was thinking that even though I have 10 more weeks left at my job before I go to Summer (intense) school, I should probably be also thinking about keeping my job, reducing my hours to about 20 a week (just to have the income), and enjoying myself while I go to class and a little less work. Hmm...still have a long way to go. Anyways...this concludes the blog for the day.\r\n\r\nTry to enjoy yourselves. Don''t do anything I would do and if you do don''t name it after me. Ha!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'college algebra,day,decisions,general blog,my day in general,nathan,school,work,', '2012-03-28 21:05:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '03', '28', '21', '05', '31', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(7, 'Organization is my Friend!', 'Today there was a lot of organization going on with my website (blog). I decided to work on the Animes page (section) by adding the animes I have watched, I am currently watching, and I will need to watch along with respective pages to them to allow me to customize each page with all kinds of things.[!--more--]\r\n<h1>Organization thing</h1>\r\nThe thing about organization for a college student that drives me insane is that when you start out with an organized pile of stuff (does that even make sense?) in about 2 or 3 weeks of constant going through that organization routine the pile starts to become a mess because you haven''t prepared for the long haul. I really wish there was some way I could organize and keep it organize.\r\n\r\nA college student needs to organize because it helps them to survive in the University or class, it allows them to know where stuff is, and it helps keep things clutter-free.\r\n<h1>Back to the day</h1>\r\nToday started out pretty decent. I got up, went to class (College Algebra) where I had a quiz in, I think I did okay but not the greatest. I have this problem when it comes to test and quizzes, I can''t seem to remember stuff (or I freeze up). Anyways, after that my mother and I went out to the store to get some important things, along with my new glasses and contacts (which cost some money), then we went to get my hair cut (which looks boss).\r\n\r\nNow I will be going to the gym to go work out for a bit, then come home to watch watch some of <a title="This Ugly Yet Beautiful World (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/this-ugly-yet-beautiful-world-anime/">This Ugly Yet Beautiful World</a> on Netflix.\r\n\r\nThat''s it! Keep it real!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'friend,general,help,my day,nathan,Netflix,organization,routine,This Ugly Yet Beautiful World,', '2012-03-29 15:48:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '03', '29', '15', '48', '18', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(8, 'My day as it normally is', 'I''m just going to go on the blog to say that today was a stimulating day for me. I got up, did my normal routine, then went to go watch so mindless television (yes I do happen to own one), and fiddle around with my 2x2x2 Rubik''s Cube just to see if I could get it down any faster. Good news about tomorrow (sunday) I am off tomorrow since I have Tier 2 Training this next week starting Monday. Yay! So I will be doing what I normally do on days where I don''t do anything.[!--more--]\r\n\r\nToday also consists of watching anime, playing some Maple, and then going to work. Eh...work. But yay it''s money! I''m so blessed to be in a job where I get paid a salary! Well...hourly paycheck but whatever.\r\n\r\nNow time to go do other stuffs. Yeah I know that this is not much of a blog, but I am just writing to keep this blog alive!\r\n\r\nAnd off to see the bright beautiful yellow sun! What am I on? Nothing! Don''t do anything I wouldn''t do, and if you do don''t name after me.\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'ahh,daily,money,my day,nathan,paycheck,rubiks,work,', '2012-03-30 04:27:47', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '03', '30', '04', '27', '47', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(9, 'The Day When Someone Wants Money From You', 'You know how some people are just hanging outside of gas station stores asking for some sort of handout? Oh...you do? Good then you know where I am going with this. :) I just don''t know. Whenever I get faced with a stranger, whom I do not know from Adam, and they try to pull some lame (maybe true) ass story out on me just to haggle me into using my debit card to get them some cash without just first asking if I had any spare change then that is just one that will not fly with me. Seriously, I do not need your sob story to allow my heart to be open to giving you my hard-earned cash. I know I might be sounding acrimonious right now but people need to learn that it doesn''t take a sob story to make someone give.[!--more--]\r\n<h1>What makes someone give money?</h1>\r\nI always like it when someone tells me up front what they want from me. Whenever they do that it is enough for my heart to open to them. When they give a sob story of some sort trying to explain to me about their personal life story before they even tell me what they want from me then I get kind of confused, I close to them, and or I start thinking whether or not their telling the truth or are they just trying to make some money off me to buy unnecessary junk.\r\n\r\nKnowing someone helps to. If I don''t who the person is, I will be less likely to give money to them.\r\nOh...the real day I had? What you don''t what to hear more? Fine...\r\nMy day started out really nice. Got up a little earlier than normal (about 10am-ish), did some cookin'' (mmm...bacon!), then went to College Algebra. After that I studied in the Library (what again? You have got to stop it now.), then I went to the Gym for the fourth week in a roll to do an intense workout. Then I went to work at 3:30pm for Tier 2 Training (yeah...more tools and more complex thing-a-ma-jigs...:/). Since then it has been eight hours and I am mentally drained. I will now go watch some <a title="Kaze no Stigma (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/af/a-z-list/kaze-no-stigma/" target="_blank">Kaze no Stigma</a>, eat some munchies, and relax.\r\n\r\nGoodnight all you who inhabit this blog! Remember: <strong>don''t do anything I wouldn''t do, and if you do don''t name it after me!</strong> Peace.\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'day,general,general day info,kaze no stigma,money,munchies,my day,nathan,', '2012-04-03 02:31:51', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '04', '03', '02', '31', '51', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(10, 'This Ugly Yet Beautiful Existence, Anime, and Cake!!!', 'So guys there is something on my heart tonight. Something that just can''t escape me. Something that seems to move me. I really have been thinking about how fragile of an existence we are in this world. What kind of a world d0 we live in where so many bad things happen? Face it. This world is such an <a title="This Ugly Yet Beautiful World (Anime)" href="http://www.nat4an.com/af/a-z-list/this-ugly-yet-beautiful-world" target="_blank">Ugly Yet Beautiful World</a> that we live and breath in.\r\n\r\nWhy do I come out and say these kinds of things on the blog? Because I am just a believer of certain things? Because I care? Because I love the world as much as it should be love? Why do I feel this way?\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">All are good questions that will one day be answered.</h2>[!--more--]\r\nNow that I think about it, people go throughout this fragile life just as it were they were the queen of some distant planet yet what it all comes down to, in the end, it doesn''t really matter. Except for one thing. How they (you) spent your life.\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Face it (again), everyone (every soul) will have to give an account of their life and how they spent it.  </strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">No matter what you did, are doing, or going to do; you will have to atone for what you have done. Now some people will have to do a little bit more work than others but as for me: I know, without a doubt, that I am covered.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;">Alright! I get it...The Day Thing...:P</h1>\r\nMy day consisted on doing the normal routine thing, well for me being in training as a Tier 2 Agent, in which I normally do. Not much to talk about. Tier 2 is starting to feel kind of like Tier 1. When you have other Tier 1 agents transfer you stuff that really should be Tier 1 only.\r\n\r\nBesides that, nothing new. Same old same old. Now going to enjoy some cake and anime. Sounds like a weird combo but what the heck! Speaking of cake: I just resurfaced an old video from a show called LazyTown that is literally the LazyTown : Cooking By The Book. Check it out! Kind of addicting yet weird at the time.\r\n\r\n[youtube id=1]UYrkQL1bX4A[/youtube]\r\nAnd then the MapleTable (Maplestory) Version! Which is much better!\r\n[youtube id=2]1pkDOrQ3lB4[/youtube]\r\nBut anyways...\r\nI am now off to have some cake and watch some anime. I just finished <a title="Kaze no Stigma (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/kaze-no-stigma-anime/" target="_blank">Kaze no Stigma</a>  so now I am probably going to watch something else. Laters and see you tomorrow!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'cake,existence,general,lazytown,maple,maplestory,mapletable,my day,my day in general,tier 2,truth,', '2012-04-04 15:18:41', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '04', '04', '15', '18', '41', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(11, 'Writing this blog from my newly acquired Laptop!!!', 'Another day down. I am now getting closer and closer to becoming a full fledged Tier 2 Agent! I am writing this blog entry from the "comfort" of my newly-acquired laptop that I just installed a copy of Fedora 16 on! It is a Lenovo 3000 N200 (Intel Pentium(R) Dual CPU T2390 @ 1.86GHz x 2) with about a GB of memory. Yeah! The memory sucks atm but I am looking into improving this baby''s performance. Hopefully I can get it to run some pretty freakin'' badass games. I am also testing the battery life on this bad boy just to see if it is good enough to take places. The only downside of this computer is I don''t think it supports two-finger scrolling (or horizontal scrolling) but I will make it work. :P[!--more--]\r\n\r\nAlong with installing Fedora 16 on my newly-acquired laptop, is to do all the tweaking one can do on a decent laptop with Fedora. I had to install Flash Plugin, Chrome, and Eclipse (not to mention Java).\r\n\r\nThen I keep on having the keys get stuck so I just take the key off and use some compressed air to clean out the junk out from them. Talk about a major overhaul on this laptop. But it is all worth it.\r\n\r\n<strong>UPDATE</strong>: I just found out that the battery life is only 3 minutes even though I charged it up all freakin'' night. So you know what that means right? Correct! I gotta go to the Interwebs Computer Store (eBay) to buy a battery for this soon-to-be beast. It looks like batteries like that for this particular model are ranging from $30 to $40. Meh...I have a job. :)\r\n\r\nSo today went well for me. Training (T2) as usual. Not anything new. I do keep on contemplating leaving the place I am at for another job but if I were to do that I would be a quitter. And I am no quitter! I won''t even quit this here blog! But I don''t know, it seems like this new T2 position will be just like T1 just because T1 Agents like to transfer T1 calls to T2 agents without telling them nothing. I can''t stand that.\r\n\r\nAnyways, I don''t really have much to say but when I do have some stuff to say I will say it here.\r\n\r\nNow time to go watch some <a title="Negima!? : Magister Negi Magi (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/negima-magister-negi-magi-anime/" target="_blank">Negima?</a> On my 300 inch screen and before that go nerd around on my newly-acquired laptop!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'day,Fedora,general,lenovo,Linux,my day in general,nathan,negima,tier 2,', '2012-04-06 17:21:40', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '04', '06', '17', '21', '40', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(12, 'OMG! Clannad Memories, The Weekend, and New Computer Parts!!!', 'I am so glad that I got the chance to spend this weekend by myself and not working (answering questions for people on the phone). It feels refreshing to do this. I think that I want to switch my schedule to a M-F 8 am to 4 pm slot when I get the chance.[!--more--]\r\n\r\nI am now listening to anime music! Right now it is <a title="Clannad (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/clannad-anime/" target="_blank">Clannad</a> <a title="Listen to the Piano Version of Clannad!" href="http://grooveshark.com/s/Toki+Wo+Kizamu+Uta+Piano+Ver/3jE0Wh?src=5" target="_blank">(piano version)</a>! It is just simply beautiful. <a title="Clannad (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/clannad-anime/" target="_blank">Clannad</a>, if you don''t already know, is a beautiful anime that just left me in tears and in an emotional depression after I finished watching it. I wanted to watch it again so bad but there was a fear that I would be in the emotional depression yet again. Depression can be one of those things that many of us go through but don''t want and have to because we need to realize that this world is an <a title="This Ugly Yet Beautiful World (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/this-ugly-yet-beautiful-world-anime/" target="_blank">Ugly Yet Beautiful World</a> and also life is beautiful no matter how many horrible, sick, twisted things there are on this God-forsaken rock.\r\n\r\nI would just like to tell you that my day has been so blessed today that I wish it were always like this! I have a new laptop that I installed Fedora 16 on and I am getting a new memory upgrade for it (specifically up to 3 GB DDR2) which will improve it''s performance tremendously. I also installed a copy of Windows 7 on VirtualBox on this laptop so that I can enjoy Windows things without worrying about viruses, adware, spyware, junk, etc.\r\n\r\nAnd now I am listening to the <a title="Listen the FULL length Shuffle! Opening song for FREE!!!" href="http://grooveshark.com/s/YOU/3r8BM4?src=5" target="_blank">Shuffle! Opening song</a>!!! I just LOVE good anime and their respective opening songs! <a title="Shuffle! (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/shuffle-anime/" target="_blank">Shuffle!</a> was a great anime that featured a great story-line, good sci-fi/fantasy magical stuff, and cute girls!!! (my favorite being kaede).\r\n\r\nWell...I just wanted to let everyone of you (all .0001%) that I am still here and I am not going anywhere. So take care, have fun, and good night!', 1, 1, 'clannad,computer,Fedora 16,fun,general,memories,my day,nathan,parts,weekend,yay,', '2012-04-08 16:32:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '04', '08', '16', '32', '19', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(13, 'Back to the Normal Routine', 'Yeah I know, it has certainly been a while since I wrote on this blog but truth is I have been extremely busy. Trying to finish up this semester, at work trying to beast at my job, and doing other important things. I have missed writing on my blog a bunch. But that was a nice break off from blogging.[!--more--]\r\n\r\nNot much going on. Just got back from playing some golf. Tomorrow I get to install my new ($$$) Audio System into my truck to make it even more bad ass. Can''t wait! A one twelve inch Polk Audio Subwoofer (360W) and a 500W Alpine AMP should do the trick in making my whole truck rubble. :P Other than that, another day today in working. Oh btw! Today is my Friday! Yeah! A whole two days off!\r\n\r\nI would really like to point out one thing about this blog: commenting. If you haven''t already found out, I created a page under "About" for rules about commenting. Take a moment to familiarize yourself with that page every few weeks because I will be updating that with what I expect in comments. You must look at that and if you didn''t know about what not to do while commenting, then tough love. I will delete your comment. So take a look at that page under "About" and I will be on later.\r\n\r\nTonight I will be playing some Dead Island on XBOX. Last night was a killer round of Halo Reach! I am almost a Warrant Officer Grade 2. Yay! Gotta get better. I also finished <a title="Rosario + Vampire (Anime)" href="http://nat4an.com/blog/rosario-vampire-anime/">Rosario + Vampire</a> (sigh). Well here is to another day and enjoy your evening!\r\n\r\nDon''t do anything I wouldn''t do. And if you do don''t name it after me!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'anime,commenting rules,dead island,featured,fun,general,golf,halo,my day,my friday,nathan,rosario,rules,', '2012-04-17 05:45:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '04', '17', '05', '45', '16', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(14, 'You can do anything that you set your mind to', 'Hello again. Nathan here with another great day of blogging. I know I haven''t been here for quite sometime, but I have an excuse as to why I was not here. My excuse: take a look around and see for yourself. I took the liberty to move my free wordpress-hosted crapping, underdeveloped blog to a more natural, free, open, and spacious self-hosted blog on my new Hosting Account with HostGator.\r\n\r\nYeah, I am not going to lie, having a website back in my control has been the best thing that has happened to me this week.  There is just something about hosting your own wordpress blog, or even hosting a self-built website, on your own server. You have more room to customize and modify your page/blog/website; You have the free reign of actually having a domain name instead of a sub-domain off another company; and it is just bada5s to own a website because of the sole reason that now a-days you would not even thing twice about whether or not you should have a website.[!--more--]\r\n\r\nAnyways, lots of new things happened to me since the last time I blog.  First off, I installed  Windows 7 Ultimate Edition (twice over) because I was running into some sort of issue that was causing a conflict with my systems (Windows 7 Ultimate Edition and Fedora 16). That issue has been resolved. Another issue, regarding computer, is that I managed to get my computer''s BIOS properly set on the timing (with memory) and overclocking (so now I am running 4 cores of 2.67 GHz as apposed to 4 cores of 2.6 GHz; Yay! A whopping .07 GHz more!!! Hey! Don''t you been laughing, at least it''s more!). Oh yeah...the timing on my memory chipset thingy. I managed to get two slightly identical chipsets 2 pairs of memory to work without crashing my computer. Yay! Of course the real test will come whenever I get the chance to play a highly intense game.\r\n\r\nTuesday (4/24/2012) went really really well. Tuesday was business-casual day at work. I also attended some Yoga classes at school to make up some absences  in my physical conditioning class. And that was pretty much it.\r\n\r\nYesterday (4/25/2012) was a decent day. Had a test in College Algebra that I felt okay on for the most part but we will find out how I did on this next monday. I got back into playing League of Legends (LoL) with Yul (my friend...yes I do have them :P), and then I came home to have a sit down dinner with the folks.\r\n\r\nToday (4/26/2012) got my Physical Conditioning paper done, turned it in, and bam! Then went to another Yoga class to make up another absence (I have been a naughty boy :P), then went to go play 9 holes of bogey golf. Well, it was bogey til I actually sunk a birdie on the 9th hole. I went crazy and from there on my day became better. Now I am writing this waiting to go to guitar practice and then Two42.\r\n\r\nThere is something I have to say about today:\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<h2>You can do anything you set your mind to</h2>\r\n</blockquote>\r\nA wise man once told me that you can do anything you set your mind to in anything subject, sport, game, or anything. I took this to heart and thought about it. Why do I give up sometimes when I am just right around the corner to victory? Just like today on the golf course. I was having a terrible day. Hitting bogey, double-bogey, triple-bogey, and the rest. I was about to quit before the last two holes. But instead I pressed on and set my mind to what I needed to do. The last hold came and there I was. On the tee box, I hit what I had thought was decent drive which turned 0ut to be a great driver. Right in the fairway. Then thought about what to hit on my second shot. I chose 8 over 7 since it would not put me over the green. I hit the ball. It flew straight and then I came up to hit the third shot thinking that I was over when out of no where I see the ball 6 inches from the hole. I was ecstatic. Tapped it in for birdie and went home.\r\n\r\nThen I thought: I guess I can do anything I set my mind to. Oh by the way, that wise person who told me about setting your mind to anything, <strong>that was my father</strong>. So thanks for being there for me dad!\r\n\r\nAnyways, now we are done. Hope you have a good one and enjoyed this post! Now I am off to guitar, then Two42. See ya!\r\n\r\nNat4an', 1, 1, 'anything,birdie,computer,father,general,golf,mind,my day,set,wisdom,yeah,you,', '2012-04-26 22:44:28', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '04', '26', '22', '44', '28', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
