(17, 'Salutations! And greetings to all who read this', 'I am writing this blog from the comfort of my office at work. Well, before I am about to clock in, so that way I am not on company''s time. That would be wrong. I am ready to go! It''s monday and I am going to help someone today.\r\n\r\nToday is a nice day. I woke up, went to class, then studied for a while, then went home, then to the gym to do a power workout. Monday''s are now going to be Manic-Power-Mondays (MpM) on this here blog where drink an energy drink and write this blog while I am on something powerful...oh a squirrel! Nice I love squirrels and there is nothing you can about it.[!--more--]\r\n\r\nI met a new friend on Kik Messenger today from across the big big blue and watery pond. Yay! Ooh...I can walk on water. Almost. Hey don''t laugh at me. What? You''re not laughing? Oh. Sad face.\r\n\r\nUm...this blog is good. Good Monday and hope to have a good shift. More later!\r\n\r\nNathan', 1, 1, 'daily,day,general,general blog,my day,my day in general,nathan,random,tier 2,work,', '2012-04-30 15:00:29', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '04', '30', '15', '00', '29', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', ''),
(18, 'How To Jailbreak iPhone 4 iPhone 3GS On iOS 5.1.1 With RedSn0w 0.9.12b8b [Windows]', 'It''s that time again when Apple has released a new firmware and Jailbreakers are desperately trying to figure out whether they should update or not. In the case of the iOS 5.1.1 firmware you <a href="http://www.ijailbreak.com/jailbreak/ios-5-1-1-jailbreak-unlock-warning-musclenerd/" target="_blank">should not update</a> until we at least get word that Pod2G''s iOS 5.1 untethered exploit will work on it. If you have accidentally updated to the iOS 5.1.1 firmware however, you will be glad to know that you can indeed Jailbreak iOS 5.1.1 tethered on your iPhone 4 or iPhone 3GS using the latest version ofRedSn0w. Thus, in this how to guide you will learn how to Jailbreak your iPhone 4 or iPhone 3GS tethered on iOS 5.1.1 using the Windows version of RedSn0w 0.9.12b8b.[!--more--]\r\n<h2>Jailbreak iPhone 4, 3GS iOS 5.1.1 Windows</h2>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 1)</strong> The first thing you will need to do is download the latest version of RedSn0w, which at the time of writing this how to guide is <strong>RedSn0w 0.9.10b8b</strong>. You can download RedSn0w 0.9.12b8b from the direct link below:\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<a href="(baseurl)files/redsn0w_win_0.9.12b2.zip" target="_blank">Download RedSn0w 0.9.12b8b (Windows)</a>\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 2)</strong> Once you have downloaded RedSn0w you will need to extract it by right clicking on the <em>redsn0w_win_0.9.10b8b.zip</em> and click the extract to folder option.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nWhen RedSn0w has been extracted find the <em>redsn0w.exe</em> file, right click on it and click the <em>Run as administrator</em> option (if applicable).\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 3)</strong> With RedSn0w running you will need to click the <strong>Jailbreak button</strong>.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 4)</strong> After clicking the Jailbreak button you will come to a screen where you will need to put your iPhone into DFU mode.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nRead through and follow the instructions presented to you which is to plug in and power off your iPhone and then click the <strong>next button</strong> when you are ready to begin the DFU mode process.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 5)</strong> When you click the next button you will need to follow the instructions presented to you in real-time to put your iPhone into DFU mode.\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hold down Power (corner) button for 5 seconds.</li>\r\n	<li>Without releasing the Power button, also hold down the Home (bottom center) button along with the Power button for 10 seconds.</li>\r\n	<li>Without releasing the home button, stop holding down the power button for up to 15 seconds.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<strong>Step 6)</strong> After you successfully enter DFU mode RedSn0w 0.9.10b8b will begin preparing your iPhone for the Jailbreak.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 7)</strong> Once RedSn0w has finished preparing your iPhone for the Jailbreak you will be asked you to specify options to go along with your Jailbreak. The only option that you actually need to make sure is checked is the Install Cydia option. Once you have ensured this option is checked, and any other options you may want, click the Next button.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 8)</strong> After you have specified your Jailbreak options you can click the <strong>next button</strong> andRedSn0w 0.9.10b8b will begin jailbreaking your iPhone. DO NOT interrupt or use the computer during this time. When your iPhone is finished being jailbroken it will boot up with the Apple logo and not go any further. This is because you have a tethered Jailbreak and you will need to put your iPhone back in DFU mode and use RedSn0w 0.9.10b8b to boot it back into a functional and Jailbroken state.\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<strong>Step 9)</strong> As explained previously when you Jailbreak your iPhone tethered you will need to plug it into your computer every time your iPhone loses power to regain all functionality. Thus, to reboot your iPhone into a functional and Jailbroken state you will need to launch RedSn0w again, click the Extras Button > then click the Just boot button and you will simply need to put your iPhone into DFU mode again.\r\n<br /><br />\r\nCongrats! You should now have a Jailbroken iPhone 4 or iPhone 3GS running the iOS 5.1.1 firmware.', 1, 2, 'break phone,hack,howto,iphone,iphone 4,jailbreak,redsn0w,tutorials,', '2012-05-09 10:42:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '05', '09', '10', '42', '42', 'yes', 'Published', 'yes', 'featured.jpg'),
(19, 'A New Day...', 'Hello again! It has been quite some time since I have last blogged. I know, I know. You missed me. But I have a legit reason for my absence. I was out of town, cleaning my room (more like purging), and I am now going to a full time schedule again.[!--more--]\r\n<h1>Going out of town</h1>\r\nThis last weekend, mother''s day weekend, I went out of town to a beautiful place out in Glen Rose, TX. By the way, happy late Mother''s Day to those mother''s who are very special to all of us. I would like to point out some really beauty aspects and benefits to going out of town this weekend.\r\n\r\n1. It allowed my to get away from it all and realize my true potential\r\n\r\n2. I just love the scenary\r\n\r\n3. I have friends who go out there and I love to see them every year\r\n\r\n4. I like change...the good kind\r\n\r\n5. Sometimes reconnecting with your inner-self is the best thing you could ever do\r\n\r\n<h1>Purging my room</h1>\r\nMy whole family decided that it was finally time to change out the nasty carpet that lined the upstairs rooms. We got brand spanking new carpet that feels like your walking on a cloud when you...well walk on it.\r\n\r\nI love the feeling because it made me and my sister both take all the crap in our rooms and closet and purge it until very little was left.\r\n\r\nWhat I am especially doing is I am inventorying my whole entire room. Starting from my computer and working my way to the right side of the room, where currently there is a pile of stuff sitting there.\r\n\r\nI never knew how much stuff I had.\r\n<h1>Back to Full Time Work</h1>\r\nI plan to go back to a full time schedule at work because I now know what kind of work I am doing and I want to occupy my time with as much stuff as I can do. Face it, if you''re going to do something for eight hours a day why not make some cash on the side? Especially at $11 an freaking hour!\r\n\r\nThe other side of a new full time schedule is a different shift. Yes I will going to a 10 am to 6:45 pm shift with Thursday and Friday off. Good for getting stuff done and then having the rest of the evening to yourself.\r\n<h1>Closing</h1>\r\nNow it is time to once again say goodbye after a long, beautiful weekend and day! I love to blog and I wish I had more time for it but when I do, I make it worth your time! I hope you enjoy and have a wonderful day!\r\n\r\nNat4an', 1, 1, 'day,full time,general,glen rose,nat4an,nathan,nature,new,new day,new place,organize,out of town,purge,rocks,texas,town,tx,work,', '2012-05-17 17:37:46', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2012, '05', '17', '17', '37', '46', 'yes', 'Published', 'no', '');
