(27, 'The Hacker with a Choice Part 1 (SSS)', '<p>Being on the run for so many years while living Ã¢â¬Åinside the codeÃ¢â¬Â as some of us would call it turned out to be a glamorous life. I was 7 when I first got a computer and was excited, really anxious, to dive right into learning the entire workings of it. I was a young William, at least what they called me at the time, who quickly learned the art of successful obstructive and elicit computer hacking.[!--more--]The first thing I would do upon powering up that ultra-sleek machine was find and launch the Terminal-based command line where I could do anything from echoing anything I typed into it to creating a small, obtrusive program to record keystrokes of fellow keyboarders who just so happened to use the library''s computer system for logging into their banks.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>At the age of 9, slightly 2 years after, my friends at school started calling me Ã¢â¬ÅWillÃ¢â¬Â because my name was apparently to long for them to spell. I would always be seen on my laptop during breaks and lunchtimes. So much to the point that they started joking around with me and saying that I was Ã¢â¬Åin the codeÃ¢â¬Â and calling me childish nicknames. Little did they know, I had the knowledge to do anything. After an intense childhood of hacking, a group know as The Anti-Hacker Elite Group (AHEG) gave me a choice, actually two, when they caught me apparently hacking into the United Nations Bank. The story to that is: one day I was at a coffee bar with my laptop scanning for people''s computers connected to the network when all of a sudden this one connection popped up with the answer to an age old question I had been looking for. For the longest time I was trying to figure out how I could ascertain monetary value from my computer skills. Long-story-short, I found the codes to the bank vault; which was not your contemporary vault but one that was a series of algorithmic pass codes on a 128-bit encryption server. I used my knowledge and tools to acquire about $3.5 million worth of goods. I was set, that is until a series of private detectives found me out. The choices they gave me were: 1. work for them - living a life under constant watch with no privacy or 2. I would be locked away in prison for the rest of my life for the millions, if not billions, of dollars I legitimately, hacked out of people bank accounts. Knowing that I wouldn''t see the end of either one of these choices or they wouldn''t favor me; I chose to make a third option: drop off the face of the planet and live underground. This was done by...wait why would I tell you guys. Ha.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>I managed to escape from the AHEG and today it is living proof that I succeeded. The AHEG continued trying to track me down but failed miserably. Now if you excuse me, since you know my story, I am late for my lunch with the queen of England that I am flying to in my privately, anonymously-owned jet that I acquired somehow with funds from an unknown source. The story to that will remain a mystery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This short story has been written by Nat4an himself apart of one of his classes. If you find any mistakes in this, please let me know by commenting. Thanks :)</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Next part/episode...</h2>\r\n<p>The story picks up with William getting on his private jet, going to Japan, after a visit with the Queen of England, for the weekend due to some unknown request from an old friend who is in need of assistance when something happens.</p>', 1, 9, 'hacker,choice,hacker with a choice,AHEG,Anti Hacker Elite Group,short,story,cool,read,more,stuff,creative,', '2013-02-16 13:37:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2013, '02', '16', '13', '37', '18', 'yes', 'Published', 'yes', 'featured.jpg'),
(29, 'A Day of Nat4an 2 or maybe it is just Nat4an', '<h1>NAT4AN.COM 2.0</h1>\r\n<p>Well, it''s not quite 2-point-O per say, but it is changing rapidly with all the new changes that are being made to it every single day. I would like to start this interesting entry of the blog (or shall I call it: In The Beginning (ITB) blog) due to the astonishing fact that I am now renaming it from it''s predeceasing form - <a href="(baseurl)(homelp)/blog/permalink/2012/03/23/Welcome-to-the-RTA@">The RTA Blog</a>. I originally started calling it The RTA Blog because I was heading out on a, what feels like now, endless road to San Angelo State University. The name stuck around for a while but I then ran into some minor setbacks and well, decided that it wasn''t proper to call it that. So I am now thinking to call it The ITB Blog because of a reason only I know. What? You want to know why? It''s nothing special. Just some idea I like. Nah...who am I kidding? You don''t want to hear why I called it that.</p>\r\n[!--more--]\r\n\r\n<h1>The Truth Revealed</h1>\r\n<p>So you decided to keep reading and you really want to know why I called it In The Beginning? Well...for you and since you are a good reader of "Cult of Nat4an" (ha ha...nah jk) I guess, I mean, I will tell ya. I named this blog In The Beginning because that resembles a very special time in this world. A time of new beginnings, fresh starts, and creations. Um...I''m talking about the creation of this world, no universe when God created the Heavens and the Earth. I am very fascinated by Creationism and what God has done. Seriously, just take a look outside at a sunset and tell me you cannot see the mighty work of God in it. Go on. Do it now!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So I decided to name this blog ITB because of the creation of something cool, new, fun, exciting, never-ending, beautiful, wonderful, and simply awestruck amazing. I recently just had a vision, no an apprehension, about what I was to do with my life, or what God called me to do. I believe I am to reach out into the darkness towards those who are lost, sick, tired, and burned out and help them come to know and understand that the party is not a party just because you get wasted, high, drunk, or whatever you kids call it these days. The party doesn''t have to be with the people who are satanical or dis-believers. The party is not in hell but in heaven and that heaven is not just a place of boringness just because there is no drinking and getting drunk. So many people in this lost world believe that hell is where the party is and "satan is my best friend" and all kinds of confusion of the sorts. It sickens me to see how this world is literally a "sick and twisted affair". I just want to be a light.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Now time for the day</h1>\r\n<p>Well, today was good and normal. Work is going smooth. Doing my thing on a project that is essentially going to be a place where people can vote on videos that are uploaded and that kinds of sorts. It''s coming along. Wish there was more money in the bank. Got about $18 in there after tossing money towards an alaskan mission trip in the summer (which I found out may be more since the plane tickets to alaska are almost going to be $1100 to $1400) which would be an amazing trip if Lord willing and He wants me to go. Um...well...what else? Worked on this site for a while. Fixing stuff. Watched some Walking Dead to which I am now caught up on. Going to go watch some more Duck Dynasty. And that is about it. Great day today! I liked it. If it is anything you should take away from this blog post, it is that - look around you and try to see your world the way it is; it might surprise you and if you happen to see a young, nice-looking, rockstar around by the name of nat4an please help him out. :) Thanks for reading and enjoy the rest of your day!</p>\r\n', 1, 1, 'nat4an,new,my day,day,general,alaska,mission trip,trip,creation,rockstar,tickets,plane,sick and twisted affair,ITB,In The Beginning,Walking Dead,Cult of Nat4an,cult,roadtoangelo,rta,simplicity,', '2013-02-21 20:56:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2013, '02', '21', '20', '56', '44', 'yes', 'Published', 'yes', 'featured.jpg'),
(30, 'Do not waste your Tax Refund and a New WITLL Framework as my day goes on', '<h4>Here ye Here ye! Come one come all and get your copy of WITLL framework! It''s FREE and under MIT License! WITLL is a Framework to Learn and to Love for web people that encapsulates the likeness of a professional web developer with the ease-of-use that is so easy even a kid can use it. Packed with all kinds of social networking features (such as built-in Tweet Display, and Social Icons Slider), SEO and Rock Solid HTML Transitional Framework, and an easy installation it is any wonder why you would want to choose something else over our framework. Besides Wordpress but that''s just for blogging. This is for websites! Yeah, we know there is squarespace but that is not like ours. That doesn''t let you see the code behind it and you get to make all kinds of epic updates to this one. Just look at this website, we used our framework.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Nah...just foolin you! I''m sorry I just had to spout out about the new web framework I have been working on. With that intro being said, let''s get down to the main topic here.</p>\r\n[!--more--]\r\n\r\n<h1>The Meat: Your Tax Refund</h1>\r\n<p>If you are like me when it comes to money then you probably have about $18 in your bank account right about now. If not, then forget I said that. :) But since you are such a good saver of the monies, you must already know exactly what you are going to do with your tax refund. Yes, that is right! Tax Season is, or was, among us. Since most of you are so anxious to spend your tax refund on useless junk, why not take into this consideration: <strong>save it</strong>. You never know what might happen and you could always use a stack of cash sitting in your bank account, in your atomic-preventive safe, or in between your worn out mattress. Why? Because of the fact that you could use that money somewhere more important such as pay last month''s rent or help pay for school tuition. Basically, no matter what you decide to do with your refund just make sure it is not going to something useless and wasteful. A good idea would be to put it into a money mutual or at least savings account to draw some interest. Me? I am going to keep my in my bank account just to save it for when I have to pay that mountainous pile of debt. Ha...I kid. But seriously, that would be a great idea if I had debt. For now I will use it for school.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>And then there was the News for today</h1>\r\n<p>So today was just a normal day, got up from an exciting night of playing Halo 4 and getting kill joys all day, and just did my normal thing. Starting getting some stuff together for the much needed organization of WITLL framework. I swear to you I have this nailed to the T now. I got Versions and Branches like no other. Good work for me. Just another day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It''s time to once again, say-goodbye. Thanks as usual for reading and enjoy your day/night/whatever.</p>', 1, 1, 'my day,day,general,witll,framework,web,swear,halo4,kill joy,tax refund,refund,money,help,save money,save,', '2013-02-24 17:29:26', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2013, '02', '24', '17', '29', '26', 'yes', 'Published', 'yes', 'featured.jpg'),
(31, 'A trip down a lane that is my own', '<p>Ever wondered what makes you remember things that you use to do, have done, in the past? Well, turns out I had one of those day. I was travelling down to the computer recycling center down by the train tracks to drop off some old company junk. When I left this massive warehouse I decided to take the street that runs into the backend of the church I use to go to.[!--more--]Of course, I saw this coming, when I approach the old church I saw that it looked very similar to how I left it all those years ago. It then began to remind me of all the good times I had there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So what makes us remember these kinds of things. Well truth is there are little things in your brain called synapses that make you "you" and contain all the information (pictures, sounds, ideas) in them. Only these pictures are not made up of conventional material that a normal computer would have, in storing pictures. The data that is contained in our brains is so much different than that of a normal computer.</p>', 1, 6, 'memory,trip,synapses,brain,company,junk,church,warehouse,computer,', '2013-03-20 17:34:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2013, '03', '20', '17', '34', '18', 'yes', 'Drafted', 'no', ''),
(33, 'How to fix iPhone Cellular Data Missing or No 4G', '<p>Hello, Nat4an, the iPhone expert here at Nat4ancorp Studios, here to talk to you about a serious issue that seems to have been plaguing a wide variety of iPhone users all over the globe. An issue that comes up with some jailbreakers and a few non-jailbreakers. An issue of most importance to our phones. An issue that is easy to fix. The issue at hand is when your iPhone displays no 3G, 4G, or LTE that which causes your iPhone to have no data service.[!--more--]\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The Story, cause everyone likes a good story...</h2>\r\n<p>One day I was minding my own business out in a less-than-urban part of town where I tend to drop a bit in and out but not to much to cause me to notice, when all of sudden my iPhone displays an "E". I thought to myself that this wasn''t much to worry about since it is just trying to search for a better signal. Once I get back into town, my iPhone usually turns back to 4G - it didn''t. This didn''t bother me too much since it may have taken a bit longer for the signal juice to start kicking in. The next day, at work while I was mucking about with web stuff, I look down at my iPhone to see that it still said "E". I quickly started to become increasingly frustrated at this issue because of the fact that I pay for 4G service and am only getting slow less-than-good quality service. Plus I was in an extremely urban part of town. After doing a bit of research, I quickly found out that the "E" meant "EDGE".</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is EDGE?</h2>\r\n<p>EDGE, which stands for Enhanced Data rates for GSM Evolution, is a faster version of GSM yet not as fast as LTE or 4G. EDGE is a high-speed 3G technology that was built upon the GSM standard. EDGE networks are designed to deliver multimedia applications such as streaming television, audio and video to mobile phones at speeds up to 384 Kbps. Such speeds still pale in comparison, though, to standard DSL and high-speed cable access today.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>That''s all well, good, and fine...but how does that affect me?</h2>\r\n<p>Well you eager beaver, it is important that I explained what EDGE was to help you understand the issue, but you are right - this doesn''t affect you, so I will move on. To continue with the story, I started experimenting with different settings in my iPhone and through me sticking to it; I was able to get 4G back on! Since there is no one single way to get your problem to magically go away because of too many oddities; Here is a list of things that I did to fix this that may help you:\r\n<br /><br />\r\n<u>For non-jailbreakers:</u>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Goto Settings > Turn on / then off Airplane Mode.</li>\r\n    <li>Goto Settings > General > Cellular > Turn Cellular Data on (if it isn''t on).</li>\r\n    <li>Goto Settings > General > Reset > Touch Reset Network Settings.</li>\r\n    <li>Goto Settings > General > Cellular > Turn Enable 3G/4G on (if it isn''t on).</li>\r\n    <li><b>If you have access</b>: Goto Settings > General > Cellular > Cellular Data Network > Scroll down to the bottom and touch Reset Settings. Then reboot your iPhone. (this was what helped me). If you see nothing in your APN Settings, this might be the route to take.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<u>For jailbreakers:</u>\r\n<br />\r\nSome extra things to do if you have a jailbroken iPhone. This can be done after doing the above for non-jailbreakers.\r\n<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Disable all jailbreaks by rebooting the iPhone, holding the + volume button upon the start up.</li>\r\n    <li>Editing the APN Settings. <b>Be careful with this one as you need to get your settings from your provider. Don''t guess at it!</b></li>\r\n    <li>Make sure the toggle for 3G is on in SBSettings. Believe it or not this has solved it.</li>\r\n    <li>You can SSH, or use iFile, to go into the root of your iPhone and replace the Carrier.plist of the ATT_US Directory with the one found in the Unknown Directory.\r\n        <br /><br />\r\n        <u>To do this (about the same for SSH):</u>\r\n        <br />\r\n        Step 1. Open iFile.\r\n        <br /><br />Step 2. Goto to / (root).\r\n        <br /><br />Step 3. Goto to User > Library > Carrier Bundle.bundle.\r\n        <br /><br />Step 4. Go up one directory to iPhone. Find Unknown.bundle and touch it.\r\n        <br /><br />Step 5. Touch the Edit button. Click the carrier.plist file. Touch the lower right icon (the clipboard). Click Copy/Link. \r\n        <br /><br />Step 6. Go back one directory to iPhone. Find ATT_US.bundle. Paste (by clicking on the lower right clipboard button) the file into this folder. <b>NOTE: You might want to backup the old carrier.plist file, just in case.</b>\r\n        <br /><br />Step 7. Reboot your phone.\r\n        <br /><br />Some have had success doing this, I myself tried this and it gave me a "3G" symbol on the top left of my iPhone but no data connection.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIf all else fails you have 2 options:\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>You can restore your iPhone. Try this one first.</li>\r\n    <li>Take it to Apple and have them fix or replace it.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>NOTE: This information was written for AT&T Customers but can be used for other carrier customers. Just replace any mention of AT&T with your carrier.</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Now that you know...</h2>\r\n<p>I hope that this article has proven to be helpful in your quest to fix your broken iPhone. Regardless of what path you take make sure to remember to troubleshoot your issue as much as you can without anyone''s help until you have exhausted all your resources. This way you learn and learning is fun! This goes for pretty much anything in life. Thanks for taking the time to read my intuitive article. Take care and have a good rest of the day!</p>', 1, 2, 'iphone,data,cellular,no 3g,no data,help,iphone help,edge,trouble with iphone,iphone 4s,iphone 5,help me,EDGE,Enhanced Data rates for GSM Evolution,Evolution,AT&T,att', '2013-04-01 19:25:51', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 2013, '04', '01', '19', '25', '51', 'yes', 'Published', 'yes', 'featured.jpg');
