(8, 'Prism (2012)', 1, 'Prism is B3atn0va''s first ever Trance/Progressive Album that is packed full of his best (so far) that he decided was good enough to slam into an album. His &quot;In The Beginning&quot; track landed pretty big, well maybe not but was hoped to, in the trance scene. Everyday he thinks of notes to put in his epic beats.', '', 4, 'Cover.jpg', 660, 645, 320, 500, 4, '2013-02-09 23:22:41', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'prism,2012,music,trance,progressive,b3atn0va,cool,epic,beats,hits,love,in the beginning', '', 'yes', 'no', 'completed', 'no', '', 'Published', '2013', '02', '09', '23', '21', '41', 'soundcloud', '11y7zeZ'),
(9, 'Video Voting System', 1, 'VVS stands for Video Voting System and it is an "as is" system for creating nice little interactive voting polls of videos for people to vote on. Includes: JWPlayer (unlicensed, but can accept license) video player (for the ability to accept uploaded videos), accepts major video format: Youtube via source, has customizable options via a conf.php file, and has a nice look and feel to it.', 'video_voting_system_1.0.zip', 1, 'vvs_capture_1.jpg', 660, 645, 320, 500, 1, '2013-03-21 18:30:39', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'video,video voting,php,system,vote system,rate system,rating videos,jquery,cool,html,nice', '<h2>Step 1: Download the source code</h2>\r\n<p>First you need to download the source code from the above Download Section File Link and save it to anywhere you want on your Desktop.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Step 2: Extract the contents of video_voting_system_x.x.zip (x''s represent version number)</h2>\r\n<p>Next, using Winzip (or any other relative zip compression program) unzip the contents to where ever you need it to go to.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Step 3: Upload/Create the Database</h2>\r\n<p>Go to your Database (these instructions assume you are using PHPMyAdmin) and click on "Databases", then click in the "Create new database" field and name your database what ever you want then click "Create". (Note: some webservers have a different method to creating a database, I would recommend consulting with your webserver administration on this.) Once you created the database, click to go into your database (if you haven''t already) and click on "Import". Click the "Choose File" and select the file "_videovotes.sql" (this is the generic baseline for the MTS; you must use this SQL unless you want to recreate the code :)). Once selected click on (on the dialog box) "Open" and then (after it closes) click on "Go". Now we are done with creating the database. We will come back here to add our reasons and staff_types and users for our system.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Step 4: Configure the props.php</h2>\r\n<p>Open up conf/props.php in Notepad or your PHP editing software (Eg. Dreamweaver). You are going to want to change some things. First change the "public $TITLE" value to the name you want displaying above the Videos. Change the "public $WEB_URL" to the landing page of your video voting system path. Next go down to a comment that says "/* DATABASE INFO */" and change the "public $DB_HOST", "public $DB_USER", "public $DB_PASS", and "public $DB_NAME" to match your credentials for your database (again consult with your webserver administration on this one). You can also change the "public $DB_PREFIX" value to match your prefix of the tables in your database. This is defaulted to "t_"</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And that is all for the conf/props.php file. Save and Close out of that.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Step 5: Place contents of index.php</h2>\r\n<p>Last thing to do is to place the Video Voting System (VVS) where you want it to display. First open up the index.php in Notepad or your PHP editing software (Eg. Dreamweaver). Now the easiest way to go about doing this is by taking everything inside of "<!-- VVS SYSTEM HEAD -->" and putting it into the <head></head> section of your document. Then take everything inside of "<!-- VVS SYSTEM BODY -->" and place it where ever you want it inside the body. You could just run the system at the path you specified to avoid confusion.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Step 6: Customize the VVS</h2>\r\n<p>Now that the initial system is setup we need to add our own customized content. All the customization can be done in the conf/props.php file. Open it up in Dreamweaver or something like that. There are comments along the way to help you understand what is what. Have fun! Once done with that, you have now customized VVS to fit your needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Step 6: Enjoy the ease-of-use of VVS!</h2>\r\n<p>Now that you have setup the entire VVS on your site, you can sit back and relax and enjoy the VVS as it takes in votes from people who vote on your videos without you even lifting a finger.</p>', 'yes', 'yes', 'in progress', 'yes', 'featured.jpg', 'Published', '2013', '03', '21', '18', '30', '39', 'none', '');
